<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FF65FED6FF722264" box="[170,201,339,365]" country="France" name="Laboratoire de Mycologie associe au CNRS" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">LY</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FF17FED7FEB32265" box="[216,264,338,364]" country="Spain" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15682" name="Real Jardín Botánico" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="Herbarium">MA</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FEDCFED6FEE82264" box="[275,339,339,365]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" name="Université Montpellier 2" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="Herbarium">MPU</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FE91FED6FED62264" box="[350,365,339,365]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FEB7FED6FE282264" box="[376,403,339,365]" country="Austria" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15588" name="Naturhistorisches Museum Wien" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="Herbarium">W</collectionCode>
, etc.). However, there are 
<specimenCount id="9D6222BEFFB9C833FD76FED7FCED2265" box="[697,854,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB9C833FCB4FED6FB9A2265" box="[891,1057,339,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aragonense">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FCB4FED6FB9A2265" box="[891,1057,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">H. aragonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
preserved in the Loscos herbarium of the 
<location id="8EBBBFECFFB9C833FF1EFEF3FCA72299" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CD5821FFBBC833FF47F9D1FF4E206D:8EBBBFECFFB9C833FF1EFEF3FCA72299" box="[209,796,374,400]" country="Spain" name="Sociedad Economica Aragonesa de Amigos del Pais" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Sociedad Económica Aragonesa de Amigos del País</location>
(Zaragoza, 
<collectingCountry id="F373A9A7FFB9C833FC6BFEF3FC522298" box="[932,1001,374,401]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Spain</collectingCountry>
). Among this material, 
<specimenCount id="9D6222BEFFB9C833FB3FFEF3FA132299" box="[1264,1448,374,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
, numbered as 1644, 1646, and 1648, were collected in “Tolocha”, the same provenance that was indicated by Scheele in the protologue (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB9C833FE45FE3BFC4222D1" author="Gonzalez Bueno, A. &amp; Munoz Garmendia, F." box="[394,1017,446,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" refId="ref7412" refString="Gonzalez Bueno, A. &amp; Munoz Garmendia, F. (2001) Francisco Loscos Bernal (1823 - 1886). Un botanico aragones. Ibercaja, Real Sociedad Economica Aragonesa de Amigos del Pais, Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid, 2 vols., 540 + 514 pp." type="book" year="2001">González Bueno &amp; Muñoz Garmendia 2001: 232–233</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen numbered 1646 could be a probable duplicate of the material preserved at 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FD00FE67FCB822F5" box="[719,771,482,508]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="Herbarium">COI</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
. However, it lacks the date of collection; but Scheele did not indicate a collection date for the gathering mentioned in the protologue. Thus, the specimen in the Loscos herbarium could be perhaps a duplicate of the specimen at 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FD6EFDAFFD6E214D" box="[673,725,554,580]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="Herbarium">COI</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDBE937FFB9C833FF72FDCAFF4E206D" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
In conclusion, as the specimen 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB9C833FDF6FDCBFDD22161" box="[569,617,590,616]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="Herbarium">COI</collectionCode>
00041604 is a complete and informative material, and matches to the traditional concept and current use of the name, we designate this specimen as the 
<typeStatus id="54DF5795FFB9C833FB80FDF7FB0D2185" box="[1103,1206,626,652]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FB2EFDF6FA2A2185" box="[1249,1425,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB9C833FB2EFDF6FA362185" box="[1249,1421,627,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aragonense">H. aragonense</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
It shows diagnostic features as the glabrous leaves on the adaxial surface, with numerous simple eglandular hairs beneath and on the margin; basal leaves 40–60 × 
<quantity id="4C9C44D2FFB9C833FDAFFD3FFD6621DC" box="[608,733,698,725]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" unit="mm" value="25.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="20.0">20–30 mm</quantity>
, ovate, lanceolate or elliptical, dentate near the base, narrowed into a conspicuous petiole; cauline leaves 0–l(–2), small; capitula 1–3, peduncles with numerous stellate and sparse glandular hairs, involucre 8–10 × 
<quantity id="4C9C44D2FFB9C833FDCEFC87FDDA2014" box="[513,609,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6–9 mm</quantity>
; phyllaries with few stellate hairs, numerous glandular hairs and sometimes a few simple eglandular hairs (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB9C833FDC2FCA3FD5D2049" author="Arvet-Touvet, C." box="[525,742,806,832]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" refId="ref6413" refString="Arvet-Touvet, C. (1913) Hieraciorum praesertim Galliae et Hispaniae catalogus systematicus. Paris, Librairie des sciences naturelles Paul Klincksiek, Paris, 480 pp." type="book" year="1913">Arvet-Touvet 1913</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB9C833FD3EFCA3FCD62049" author="Zahn, K. H." box="[753,877,806,832]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" pagination="1 - 492" refId="ref9642" refString="Zahn, K. H. (1930) Hieracium. In: Ascherson, P. &amp; Graebner, P. (Eds.) Synopsis der mitteleuropaischen Flora 12 (1). Gebruder Borntraeger, Leipzig, pp. 1 - 492." type="book chapter" year="1930">Zahn 1930</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB9C833FCB7FCA3FBFA2049" author="Sell, P. D. &amp; West, C." box="[888,1089,806,833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" pagination="358 - 410" refId="ref9011" refString="Sell, P. D. &amp; West, C. (1976) Hieracium L. In: Tutin, T. G., Heywood, V. H., Burges, N. A., Moore, D. M., Valentine, D. H., Walters, S. M. &amp; Webb, D. A. (Eds.) Flora Europaea, vol. 4. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, pp. 358 - 410." type="book chapter" year="1976">Sell &amp; West 1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB9C833FB83FCA2FA862049" author="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F." box="[1100,1341,806,833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" refId="ref8422" refString="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F. del (2017) Estudio monografico de los generos Hieracium y Pilosella en Espana. Con referencias a Portugal y los Pirineos franceses. Monografias de Botanica Iberica, nº 20, Jolube, Jaca, 422 pp." type="book" year="2017">Mateo &amp; Egido 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Mateo 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB9C833FA58FCA2FF25206D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">et al</emphasis>
. 2017).
</paragraph>
